comments.body:
@cwulfman the images we care about for PGP are the ones that are listed in the PGP metadata spreadsheet you have linked in the description above. Filter by JTS for Library and then match on Shelfmark.  

I don't know if there are images beyond what's in the spreadsheet that are relevant for PGP.

I understand from the PGP team that archival designation of recto/verso doesn't always match scholar determination of recto/verso, but where the images indicate recto/verso according to JTS, it would be nice to have access to that information in some structured way (preferably image label, for consistency with Cambridge geniza materials).
